.TH "vfs_setpos" 9 "vfs_setpos" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vfs_setpos \- update the file offset for lseek
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "loff_t" vfs_setpos
.BI "(struct file *file "  ","
.BI "loff_t offset "  ","
.BI "loff_t maxsize "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "file" 12
file structure in question
.IP "offset" 12
file offset to seek to
.IP "maxsize" 12
maximum file size
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This is a low-level filesystem helper for updating the file offset to
the value specified by \fIoffset\fP if the given offset is valid and it is
not equal to the current file offset.

Return the specified offset on success and -EINVAL on invalid offset.
